name: North Node
archetype: The Soul's Evolutionary Direction, Future Self, Dharmic Path
functionAndMeaning: Your soul's intended growth direction in this lifetime. The North Node represents the qualities, experiences, and consciousness you're meant to develop. It points toward your dharmic path - often feeling unfamiliar or challenging because it requires you to stretch beyond past-life patterns. This is your cosmic GPS toward soul evolution.
contemplationQuestions: What qualities is my soul calling me to develop?
How can I move toward my growth edge with courage?
What unfamiliar territory is my dharma asking me to explore?
giftExpression: Courageous soul growth, dharmic alignment, evolutionary leadership, conscious development of new capacities, spiritual pioneering
shadowExpression: Avoiding growth challenges, clinging to South Node comfort zone, fear of the unknown, resistance to soul evolution, spiritual stagnation

name: South Node
archetype: The Soul's Inherited Gifts, Past Mastery, Karmic Comfort Zone
functionAndMeaning: Your soul's accumulated wisdom and natural talents from past experiences. The South Node represents what you've already mastered and can easily access - your gift treasury. While these are your superpowers, over-relying on them can keep you from North Node growth. The art is using South Node gifts to serve North Node evolution.
contemplationQuestions: What natural gifts do I possess?
How can I use my inherent talents to serve my soul's growth?
What patterns am I ready to transform while honoring my gifts?
giftExpression: Mastery in service of evolution, natural talents supporting dharmic path, wisdom integration, effortless expertise, karmic gifts
shadowExpression: Over-reliance on past patterns, avoiding growth challenges, spiritual bypassing through natural talents, karmic loops, comfort zone addiction

name: Lilith
archetype: The Wild Feminine, Primal Power, Shadow Sovereignty
functionAndMeaning: Your raw, untamed feminine power and the parts of yourself that refuse to be controlled or diminished. Lilith represents your primal instincts, sexual sovereignty, and the wild wisdom that emerges when you refuse to be domesticated. This energy transcends gender - it's about reclaiming your authentic power and saying 'no' to diminishment.
contemplationQuestions: Where do I give my power away to please others?
What wild aspects of myself am I ready to reclaim?
How can I express my authentic power with wisdom?
giftExpression: Authentic sovereignty, healthy boundaries, primal wisdom, fearless authenticity, sacred wildness, sexual empowerment, untamed creativity
shadowExpression: Destructive rebellion, manipulation, victim consciousness, suppressed rage, sexual power games, vindictive behavior, chaotic wildness

name: Chiron
archetype: The Wounded Healer, Sacred Wound, Healing Mastery
functionAndMeaning: Your core soul wound that becomes your greatest healing gift. Chiron represents the area where you experience ongoing sensitivity and challenge, yet through embracing this wound with compassion, you develop profound healing abilities. Your deepest pain becomes your medicine - for yourself and others who carry similar wounds.
contemplationQuestions: What wound has been my greatest teacher?
How has my pain developed into wisdom?
How can I serve others through my own healing journey?
giftExpression: Compassionate healing presence, wisdom through experience, helping others heal similar wounds, transformed pain into medicine, wounded healer mastery
shadowExpression: Playing victim to the wound, avoiding healing work, projecting pain onto others, spiritual bypassing, chronic wounds, martyrdom

name: Part of Fortune
archetype: The Prosperity Point, Material Blessing, Integrated Success
functionAndMeaning: The sweet spot where your spirit (Sun), soul (Moon), and personality (Ascendant) harmoniously combine to create material and spiritual abundance. The Part of Fortune shows where you can find natural success, prosperity, and joy when you integrate all parts of yourself authentically.
contemplationQuestions: How can I align my spirit, emotions, and personality for authentic success?
Where do I find natural prosperity and joy?
What integration brings me the greatest fulfillment?
giftExpression: Holistic success, integrated abundance, natural prosperity, joy through authentic expression, aligned manifestation, harmonious achievement
shadowExpression: Chasing external success without inner alignment, material focus without spiritual integration, compartmentalized living, fortune seeking without authenticity

name: Vertex
archetype: The Magnetic Destiny Point, Fated Encounters, Soul Magnetism
functionAndMeaning: Your electromagnetic point of destiny where significant soul encounters and fated experiences are drawn to you. The Vertex represents what you magnetically attract when you're aligned with your authentic path - often bringing people and experiences that catalyze major life changes or soul recognition moments.
contemplationQuestions: What types of people and experiences do I magnetically attract?
How do fated encounters serve my soul's evolution?
What is my energy field calling into my life?
giftExpression: Conscious magnetism, embracing destined connections, soul recognition, aligned attraction, evolutionary encounters, destiny acceptance
shadowExpression: Avoiding destined encounters, resistance to fated changes, unconscious magnetism, victimhood around attractions, fear of destiny

name: Ascendant
archetype: The Persona, Life Approach, Soul's Chosen Mask
functionAndMeaning: The energetic signature you radiate and how you spontaneously approach life. Your Ascendant is the soul's chosen costume for this incarnation - the energy you embody to navigate the world and initiate new experiences. It's your first impression and your instinctive way of engaging with life.
contemplationQuestions: How do others first experience my energy?
What approach to life feels most natural to me?
How does my outer presentation serve my soul's journey?
giftExpression: Authentic self-presentation, conscious persona choice, natural life approach, inspiring first impressions, aligned energy radiation, spontaneous authenticity
shadowExpression: False personas that hide authentic self, reactive responses, unconscious projection, mask becoming prison, identity confusion

name: Midheaven
archetype: The Calling, Public Purpose, Highest Achievement
functionAndMeaning: Your soul's calling in the public sphere and how you're meant to contribute to collective evolution. The Midheaven represents your highest potential achievement, career fulfillment, and the legacy you're here to build. It's where your private development meets public service.
contemplationQuestions: What is my soul's calling in the world?
How am I meant to serve the collective?
What legacy do I want to leave through my work and public contribution?
giftExpression: Aligned public service, authentic authority, meaningful career, inspiring leadership, purposeful achievement, legacy consciousness, vocational mastery
shadowExpression: Ego-driven ambition, public image over authentic calling, avoiding public responsibility, career disconnected from purpose, status obsession
